subject: p14841168
History: Syncope and cough for five days.
Findings: Frontal and lateral views of the chest were obtained. The lateral views are somewhat underpenetrated in part due to the patients overlying arm. Given this, there is persistent mild elevation of the right hemidiaphragm. Minimal left basilar atelectasis is seen. There is no focal consolidation. No large pleural effusion is seen. Slight blunting of the right costophrenic angle is chronic. The cardiac and mediastinal silhouettes are grossly stable as comparison with. No overt pulmonary edema is seen.
Impression: Likely left basilar atelectasis. Otherwise, no acute cardiopulmonary process.
